tweet: As for logistics: current workers at $MCD, for example, would see no change in their paychecks, but they would have an app that tracks their biweekly purchases of $MCD stock.   They would also have the option of using the app as their main investing brokerage account.

name: Masa Capital
tweet: A minimum wage hike is digestible by megacorps like $MCD that can handle it, while pressuring small businesses that already have many disadvantages, including shutdowns.  This policy removes the negative of small businesses having to raise labor costs on already thin profits.

name: Masa Capital
tweet: Instead of raising the minimum wage to $15/hour in all states, I have a better solution to help the "wealth gap" that also helps small business: every hourly worker at a public company like $MCD gets a 15% raise payable in company stock that must be held for at least one year.
